**Queue using Two Stacks**

A queue is a data structure that follows the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) principle, where elements are added to the end of the queue and removed from the front.

In this implementation, we will use two stacks to simulate a queue. One stack will be used to store the elements that are waiting to be added to the queue, and the other stack will be used to store the elements that are currently in the queue.

